I"<p>Most <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/neurotransmitters-and-hormones-are-means-of-biochemical-signaling">hormones</a> are either secreted by specialized neurons in certain <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/triune-brain-model-classifies-brain-regions-through-evolutionary-lens">brain regions</a>, or are secreted as a cascade effect of <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/neurotransmitters-and-hormones-are-means-of-biochemical-signaling">hormones</a> secreted by such cells. <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/brains-are-like-monkeys-with-supercomputers">Subcortical</a> regions are particularly involved in <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/neurotransmitters-and-hormones-are-means-of-biochemical-signaling">hormone</a> secretion.</p>
